						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying on the boundary between the village and Durgi village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1557, Yuva, Nija-Bhādrapada, śu. 2, Thursday, corresponding to 1635 A.D., September 3.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. States that while Nāyapa-Nāyani Veṅkaṭapati-Nāyanivāru was governing Mācherlasīma the boundary between the villages Durgi and Ātukūru was marked with a <hi rend="italic">jayastaṁbha.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
